frus:attachment.p:
“Whereas the American Government proclaimed to the world that Cuba is, and of
                        right ought to be, free and independent, by a joint resolution in pursuance
                        of which it declared war against Spain, and sent its Army and Navy to fight
                        for the rights of the Cuban people until a complete victory was gained,
                        which culminated in the evacuation of the island by the Spanish forces, the
                        flags of both American peoples being unfurled to the breeze;
